{
  "text": "The governing equations are written in the streamfunction-vorticity form for laminar flow regime and are twodimensional. Navier-Stokes equations in the streamfunction-vorticity form are written as Eqs. (1)- (3) for a steady, incompressible, Newtonian fluid with the Boussinesq approximation [CITATION_1] . Furthermore, it is assumed that radiation heat exchange is negligible and that gravity acts in a vertical direction.",
